Yes, Flutter allows for the creation of named routes using the MaterialApp's
onGenerateRoute property.


A STEP-BY-STEP LOOK

 1. In the App's main.dart, define the MaterialApp.
 2. Set the onGenerateRoute and initialRoute properties.
 3. Optionally create a separate file to define the route configurations and
    load them using import or part.
 4. Use Navigator with the unique route name to navigate to the intended screen.


FLUTTER CODE EXAMPLE

Here is the Flutter code:

 1. main.dart
 2. myHomePage.dart

MAIN.DART

Use the following Dart code:

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'myHomePage.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      // Assigns the 'home' route as the initial route
      initialRoute: '/home',
      // The `onGenerateRoute` function takes a callback `settings` which contains the named route
      onGenerateRoute: (RouteSettings settings) {
        switch (settings.name) {
          case '/home':
            return MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => MyHomePage());
          case '/details':
            // You can pass any arguments to the named route
            var arguments = settings.arguments;
            return MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => DetailsScreen(arguments));
          default:
            return null;
        }
      },
    );
  }
}


